sapphire-pound19 (1.9.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Rename sapphire-specific package to sapphire-pound
  * Package K12 Systems modifications to pound in Debian format.
    More information can be found at http://users.k12system.com/mrwizard/pound/
  * This is for the older release of Pound, 1.9.1.  No new features have been added
    in quite some time.
  * ForeHTTP10 and SSLUncleanShutdown support
  * ControlUser, ControlGroup, and ControlMode directives
  * URL Rewrite changes - fixes for splitDNS, comparisons against global listeners and port checking
  * Session management enhancements - track hits, users, url, etc.
  * Base64 fixes for URL Escaping
  * AuthType decoding, including Sapphire/CF authentication support
  
 -- Joseph Gooch <mrwizard@k12system.com>  Mon, 15 Mar 2010 16:23:12 -0500

